column5: So we finally got out there fished for a couple of hours, Had a good time then went home.    This one is my wifes, bigger than the one I caught. Just using canned corn for those who care. Bonus a Large mouth nailed my corn as it hit the water. no picture as it's out of season so quickly released.

That's a nice sized carp, and looks like a decent day to fish as well. I've yet to have a largemouth that smashed my "top-water-corn" but I have heard it happen, pretty funny indeed.  Just a side note though, if you're not planning to keep them, try to avoid holding them by the gill plate.  Thanks for the report.
Nice fish and thanks for the report.
Well aint that a long story short lol  Cool fish
Absolutely. Lord knows they're such incredibly rare and fragile fish.   (Short and to the point, nice report.  )

Your right Victor. Usually I don't even take them out of the water, I just reach down with my pliers and remove the hook, We just did this for the pics The area is just south of the cn tracks it's pretty boring to look at really
Nice looking carp, congrats to your wife!  Glad to hear that you got into a few.
Great report and pic jsh That is a beauty for sure!!! Congratulations to your wife for landing this brute Leechman
